    "recap_headline": "Seton Hall University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "South Orange, N.J. \u2013\nFrankie Scrivanic\ndrove home what proved to be the game-winning run in the bottom of the eighth inning as the Seton Hall baseball team opened its weekend series with a win over Hofstra, 5-4.\nHow it Happened\nAfter Pirate starter\nSteven Svenson\nworked around a jam in the top of the first, his offense spotted him an early lead in the bottom half. After\nAiden Dill\nreached on an error and stole second to lead off the frame,\nGabe Cavazzoni\ndoubled him home to give Seton Hall an early 1-0 lead. Two batters later,\nRyan Frontera\ndid the same by doubling down the right field line to bring home\nAidan Sengenberger\nfrom first.\nB1 | Gabe gets us going early with an RBI double \ud83d\udc4d\npic.twitter.com/b85Ggcr9mq\n\u2014 Seton Hall University Baseball (@SHUBaseball)\nMarch 20, 2026\nLead \u27a1\ufe0f Doubled \u2705\nRyan Frontera\ncaps a two-run first inning with an RBI double to right!\npic.twitter.com/8zBJzAvXmS\n\u2014 Seton Hall University Baseball (@SHUBaseball)\nMarch 20, 2026\nAfter retiring the side in order in the second, Svenson surrendered his first run of the game in the third on a sacrifice fly to center. However, the Preseason BIG EAST Pitcher of the Year would limit the damage there, keeping the Pride bats silent for the remainder of his five-inning outing.\nIn the bottom of the fifth, Sengenberger added to The Hall's lead with an RBI single to left. Again with a two-run advantage, the Pirates called upon\nDerek Benzinger\nto navigate them to a win. The graduate student worked a clean sixth, but Hofstra got to him in the seventh for three runs to take the lead, 4-3.\nIn the bottom of the seventh, Seton Hall answered right back. Productive outs were the name of the game, as Dill laid down a sacrifice bunt to move\nJake Lopez\nand\nTommy Manzo\ninto scoring position. Cavazzoni then grounded out to shortstop, allowing Lopez to score the tying run.\nIn the eighth, Seton Hall would vault itself back into the lead for good. After\nTy Acker\nreached on an error and\nNick Tomasetto\nsingled, a base hit from Scrivanic brought home Acker and gave the Pirates a 5-4 edge. That would prove to be enough, as\nJohn Higgins\nstruck out two in a 1-2-3 ninth inning to earn his sixth save of the season.\nScriv gives us the lead in the 8th!\n#NeverLoseYourHustle\npic.twitter.com/WuTTvZGvCT\n\u2014 Seton Hall University Baseball (@SHUBaseball)\nMarch 20, 2026\nUp Next\nSeton Hall will celebrate Senior Day on Saturday prior to the middle game of its series with Hofstra which is slated for 1 p.m.",
